"Chaos and Order are not enemies, only opposites." -Richard Garriott

“Order and disorder', said the speaker, 'they each have their beauty.” 
― Orson Scott Card, Speaker for the Dead

“Every morning I jump out of bed and step on a landmine. The landmine is me. After the explosion, I spend the rest of the day putting the pieces together.” 
― Ray Bradbury, Zen in the Art of Writing

“Our real discoveries come from chaos, from going to the place that looks wrong and stupid and foolish.” 
― Chuck Palahniuk, Invisible Monsters

“The only order in the universe is just a cycle of calm and chaos.” 
― Toba Beta, Master of Stupidity cha

“Chaos was the law of nature; Order was the dream of man.” 
― Henry Adams, The Education of Henry Adams

"What we call chaos is just patterns we haven't recognized. What we call random is just patterns we can't decipher. what we can't understand we call nonsense. What we can't read we call gibberish."
― Chuck Palahniuk, Survivor

“I accept chaos, I'm not sure whether it accepts me.” 
― Bob Dylan



